post_text: Mackinaw City Public School is excited to announce that we are able to continue distributing food bundles through the Summer Food program. This program will start on Tuesday, July 7 and continue until Tuesday, September 1. This program will be a little different than the Emergency Food program. The program will still be 7 breakfasts and 7 lunches but we will no longer be able to deliver food bundles. All participants must pick up food bundles at the school. We will have the food bundles available earlier for any one who will need to pick up before going to work. Food bundles will be available from 7:45-10:30 am on Tuesdays. If you have any questions or would like to be removed from the program, please call 231-436-8211.

We plan to continue the instruction we have been providing since school closed in March. Communications from the school and your child‚Äôs teachers will be sent out next week discussing expectations while this closure continues.

We are also working through how to restore many of our Spring activities such as graduation.

Please stay home, stay safe and know we as educators are here to support your families. If needs arise please contact Jeff Curth or
